b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Lexica is best suited for prompt discovery, image search, inspiration, Stable Diffusion users, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. PhotoRoom, meanwhile, shines for product photography, background removal, ecommerce listings, social media, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2022, Lexica describes itself as \"AI image search engine and generator for finding prompt inspiration.\" PhotoRoom, established in 2020, positions itself as \"AI photo editor specialized in product photography and backgrounds.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **PhotoRoom** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 6.0), more features (5 vs 3), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Lexica is a poor choice — far from it. Lexica excels in its own right, particularly for prompt discovery and image search.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value best-in-class background removal, go with PhotoRoom. If massive searchable database of ai images and prompts matters more to you, Lexica is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
